<div id="review_2147316003" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2147316003" />
    <a title="Apratim Mukherjee" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/51748820-apratim-mukherjee"><img alt="Apratim Mukherjee" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1622563693p2/51748820.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2147316003?book_show_action=true">Oct 19, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Apratim Mukherjee" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Apratim Mukherjee" href="/user/show/51748820-apratim-mukherjee">Apratim Mukherjee</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780141034065" href="/book/show/6743025-the-siege-of-mecca">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2147316003" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1633825862903024175">It is very hard to rate a book which turns out to be the only reliable source about the siege of Mecca in 1979.This topic is hardly discussed in or for that matter even remembered by today&apos;s world.Saudi Arabia did a great job by erasing this incident out of the public memory.This meant that the author had to take a lot of pain in order to complete his work.The book also criticises the house of Saud in particular and Saudi establishment in general due to their failure on various fronts and making</span>
  <span id="freeText1633825862903024175" style="display:none">It is very hard to rate a book which turns out to be the only reliable source about the siege of Mecca in 1979.This topic is hardly discussed in or for that matter even remembered by today's world.Saudi Arabia did a great job by erasing this incident out of the public memory.This meant that the author had to take a lot of pain in order to complete his work.The book also criticises the house of Saud in particular and Saudi establishment in general due to their failure on various fronts and making a country their(Al Saud's) family business.Further,it also explains in short about significance of Kaaba,how the movement sowed seeds for modern terrorist organisations and how Jimmy Carter performed in the middle east<br /> It is a excellent book with a bit of dodgy editing and missing some pictures.It is a must read for anyone interested in modern history of Saudi Arabia from a neutral perspective.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1633825862903024175" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


