<span id="freeTextContainer6437057762908850567">The siege of the Muslim shrine in Mecca, Saudi Arabia in 1979 was not as publicized in the West as the Iran hostage crisis, which was taking place at the same time. Both were world-shaking events, but the Siege, as explained by author Trofimov, was the tip of the iceberg that propelled many violent anti-West actions in the Middle East and continue to this day. <br/><br/>Siege is an excellent and concise education of Muslim sects and Saudi royalty/religious-based government. It explains the US’s incompeten</span>
  <span id="freeText6437057762908850567" style="display:none">The siege of the Muslim shrine in Mecca, Saudi Arabia in 1979 was not as publicized in the West as the Iran hostage crisis, which was taking place at the same time. Both were world-shaking events, but the Siege, as explained by author Trofimov, was the tip of the iceberg that propelled many violent anti-West actions in the Middle East and continue to this day. <br /><br />Siege is an excellent and concise education of Muslim sects and Saudi royalty/religious-based government. It explains the US’s incompetence in understanding Middle East motivations during the Carter administrative. The trickle down effect caused by the Siege - the burning of the American embassy in Pakistan, riots in India, the attempted assassination of Pope John Paul II, and most importantly, the manipulation of the event by Iran’s Ayatollah Khomeini - all make sense after the siege. <br /><br />It’s incomprehensible that religion and government are not separated in Saudi Arabia. <br /><br />Thanks to Mikey B.for bringing this excellent book to my attention. Highly recommended to anyone interested in world politics.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6437057762908850567" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


