        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer133825571" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10005553896848976813">This book was shocking for me, not because of the sad events and stories it tells, but because of the fact that almost no one I know (including myself) knew about what happened in the holiest place on earth in the late 70&apos;s of the 20th century, which showed that history can be forgotten, or made forgotten as I suspect is the case with this incident.<br/><br/>It also explained to me the reason behind the heightened security measures I see in Al-Masjid Al-Haram, a place so holy, that even scaring the pigeon</span>
  <span id="freeText10005553896848976813" style="display:none">This book was shocking for me, not because of the sad events and stories it tells, but because of the fact that almost no one I know (including myself) knew about what happened in the holiest place on earth in the late 70's of the 20th century, which showed that history can be forgotten, or made forgotten as I suspect is the case with this incident.<br /><br />It also explained to me the reason behind the heightened security measures I see in Al-Masjid Al-Haram, a place so holy, that even scaring the pigeons around it is considered a sin, which makes harming humans in this place almost unimaginable.<br /><br />By the time I reached the end of this book, I wasn't sure what made me more angry, the shocking events that happened inside the holy mosque of Mecca, or the way the local authorities choose to solve it, first by surrounding the whole story under a veil of secrecy, and secondly by choosing to ask for the aid of France and refusing to engage the Jordanians, Moroccans or Egyptians, simply because they couldn't trust that these "sister" states will not claim right of the holy city after helping in freeing it.<br /><br />I'm a firm believer that without a real knowledge and understanding of our history, any attempt to interpret our present is impossible. This book is an important peace of the puzzle, and a definite recommended read.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10005553896848976813" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


