        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1085862053" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16820694166646751628">Outstanding. I&apos;ve done in depth studies of the Iran Hostage Shebang back in &apos;79 but I was never fully aware of the fact that the entire region was on the verge of apocalypse during the same days (nothing new under the sun, right?)<br/><br/>Not just the fact that the most intensely regarded holy place in the world was a deadly warzone for roughly a week with a virtual media blackout but other little things - like the fact that our embassy in Paksistan was burned to the ground, causing American and Pakistan</span>
  <span id="freeText16820694166646751628" style="display:none">Outstanding. I've done in depth studies of the Iran Hostage Shebang back in '79 but I was never fully aware of the fact that the entire region was on the verge of apocalypse during the same days (nothing new under the sun, right?)<br /><br />Not just the fact that the most intensely regarded holy place in the world was a deadly warzone for roughly a week with a virtual media blackout but other little things - like the fact that our embassy in Paksistan was burned to the ground, causing American and Pakistani casualties but almost no one noticed because the media was focused on living hostages in Iran rather than dead ones elsewhere. <br /><br />It was more dramatic I suppose, so points to all media on that aspect. I somehow missed the big picture regarding these significant simultaneous events while researching the hostage crisis in Iran. I was aware of them, but not their ultimate significance.<br /><br />The '79 revolution was a time of ultimate confusion. The author of this book is on the WSJ staff so you have to expect a little conservative spin and a flat out disgust of Jimmy Carter. Luckily, I think he's the greatest disaster in 20th century American leadership so the author gets a pass on that. If you disagree with me, please don't argue with me. I'm tired.<br /><br />THIS READS LIKE A THRILLER.<br /><br />If you enjoy thriller type shit and have a moderate interest in current events, and can tolerate minimal right wing spin, you should read this. The facts outweigh the partisan perspective. I have learned a lot more than I thought I already knew. This goes to the favorites shelf.<br /><br /></span>
