  <span id="freeText15321988315959534126" style="display:none">Surprisingly good, despite the pulpy title and pulpy writing; of all of the books I have ever read about Saudi Arabia, it is the one I would most recommend to someone trying to understand why Saudi Arabia is the way it is now. Very well-researched, catching small but critical points that have eluded many other Western writers, even several good ones. And the subject matter needs no exaggeration - it's absolutely fascinating. My one complaint would be the melodramatic writing style, but that's a small gripe.</span>
