  <span id="freeText15558696659681492535" style="display:none">Set during November of 1979 former National Guard self proclaimed "Mahdi," Juhayman al-Otaybithe and his acolytes seize control of Islam's holiest sites in Mecca. The predecessor of Osama Bin Laden's Al Qaida, and Abu Bakr Al Baghdadi's ISIS/Daesh smuggled assault weapons and ammunition in coffins demanding the immediate overthrow of the Saudi Royal family. The group consisted of Saudi tribesmen, African American converts, and Indian/Pakistani madrassa students of the Wahabi school of thought. Having chained the gates of the Grand Mosque positioned snipers on top of minarets over 100,000 pilgrims were trapped between armed militants and Saudi security forces. Failed attempts by Saudi, Pakistani and French commandos were made to recapture the Kaaba ended in failure. Eventually most of the pilgrims were granted permission to leave if they had sworn their allegiance to the self proclaimed Mahdi and many days of the siege ended with a fatal gas being used to clear the site. Most of the Juahman's followers were killed in fierce clashes with the remainder beheaded publically including their leader.</span>
