    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_293174864" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/293174864" />
    <a title="Jerome" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7672919-jerome"><img alt="Jerome" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1330740421p2/7672919.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/293174864?book_show_action=true">Mar 12, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jerome" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jerome" href="/user/show/7672919-jerome">Jerome</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer293174864&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer293174864" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8122657303368446509">Pulpy but very interesting. Tons of detail, too, just what I look for in a book like this.<br/>I first read about this incident in <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/110890.The_Looming_Tower_Al_Qaeda_and_the_Road_to_9_11' title='The Looming Tower Al-Qaeda and the Road to 9/11 by Lawrence Wright' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Looming Tower: Al-Qaeda and the Road to 9/11</a>. I felt so stupid not knowing anything about it before. Too bad most people still don&apos;t know about it. The book is a bit melodramatic and has a hyperventilating tone, which I didn&apos;t like, though. He also tries to establish a clear, definitive link between the incident and the onset of Islamist militancy in the Middle East, </span>
  <span id="freeText8122657303368446509" style="display:none">Pulpy but very interesting. Tons of detail, too, just what I look for in a book like this.<br />I first read about this incident in <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/110890.The_Looming_Tower_Al_Qaeda_and_the_Road_to_9_11" title="The Looming Tower Al-Qaeda and the Road to 9/11 by Lawrence Wright" rel="nofollow noopener">The Looming Tower: Al-Qaeda and the Road to 9/11</a>. I felt so stupid not knowing anything about it before. Too bad most people still don't know about it. The book is a bit melodramatic and has a hyperventilating tone, which I didn't like, though. He also tries to establish a clear, definitive link between the incident and the onset of Islamist militancy in the Middle East, but the event was largely symbolic for the most part, so that approach had a clumsy, stilted feel to it. He also describes the Islamabad embassy siege, and tries to connect that to the events in Mecca, ending with the same effect. The book also reads like a long magazine article. <br />What also annoyed me was the author's occasional and largely irrelevant political assertions, disguised as analysis. The more serious and fundamental flaw of the book is its inability to back up its thesis. The thesis set out by the author in the beginning of the book is that the siege of Mecca had far reaching implications that have been largely forgotten. However, after having completed the book, this thesis was never even mentioned again by the author.<br />Still worth a read, though.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8122657303368446509" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

